Safe journies! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udaleb123.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Daleb123</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 166<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/11/02 1:00:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1691.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Weapons</span><hr size=1> By current standards, Monk fists are awful weapons (see the fists damage chart at <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=70">www.monkly-business.com/a...icleNum=70</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> ). Also, note that your weapon skills have a higher cap at Level 50 than Hand to Hand (see the skills chart at <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.monkly-business.com/articles2.asp?ArticleNum=68">www.monkly-business.com/a...icleNum=68</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> ).<br>
<br>
You can easily obtain better weapons and fight more effectively with them, so why would you not want to? As a melee class, you should practice ALL of your melee skills. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uroyceli.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Royceli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(7/11/02 1:26:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1691.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Weapons</span><hr size=1> All the above.  Like Daleb said, it's important to practice all your weapon skills.  Although your fists are terrible to start out with (and other hand to hand weapons aren't much better), when you get your epic your fists become 9 dmg 16 dly killing machines.  With the clickable haste of the epic and another haste item, you can punch your way thru almost any mob.  It would suck to get your epic and swing like crazy, but not be able to hit anything because you never practiced your skill.  But of course you can't ignore your blunt skills either.  There are some great blunt weapons later on and most low-mid level monks use 1 hand blunt weapons for most of their life.  Unlike fists and 2 hand weapons, there seems to a good supply of 1 hand blunts out there that you can progress through from lvl 1 -60.  But then of course there is the 2 hand blunt weapons as well.  These can be devastating weapons in the hands of a monk. Although fairly expensive and hard to acquire for a low-level monk (plus not as effective due to damage caps), there are several weapons later on for monk use (ie.  Wu's Quivering Staff, Peacebringer, Imbued Fighter's Staff).  I also have to mention the Tranquil Staff.  I'm still waiting to get my hands on one of these, but parses from other monks have indicated that this bad boy regularly outdamages epic monks dual-wielding their fists and/or good 1 hand blunts.  It does amazing damage and is something to really look forward to.  So like hand to hand, it is an important skill to practice for later use.<br>
<br>
For now, you should probably get a cheap one hand blunt and wield a wep (or fist) in your primary hand until you max the skill each level and then switch hands.  2 hand blunt is a little hard to work on since most of the weapons available to you at this stage will do terrible damage and won't help you too much in a tough fight.  A good weapon for practicing skill is the bamboo bo stick 8/20, since it if very quick (more swings = more chances to get skill up) but unfortunately will not do much damage.  I used to beat on a mob with my fist and a 1 hand blunt weapon, and then switch to my 2 hander once he started running.  Hopefully, this will keep your skills going strong.  Good luck. <p>Royceli, Lvl 51 Human Monk <BR>
